        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload /LEG_04_Contract_Backlog_Tracker.xlsx to Analyst. Across the Contract Backlog, Approval Pipeline AND Ageing Analysis tabs, calculate the absolute number and percentage of contracts pending more than 30, 60, and 90 days for each of the 11 divisions, identify the 3 divisions with the largest unsigned-value exposure in MYR millions, and quantify the total commercial risk from the 340-agreement backlog. Build (1) a horizontal bar chart of unsigned contract value by division ranked worst to best, and (2) a 100% stacked column chart showing each division\'s contribution to the overall backlog. Flag divisions with more than 50 contracts pending as Red, 25-50 as Amber, and below 25 as Green. Output as a RAG dashboard with both charts embedded and one recommended fast-track action per Red division.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload /LEG_05_Regulatory_Inquiry_Log.xlsx to Analyst. Cross-reference the Inquiry Tracking, Document Production AND Response Timeline tabs to identify which regulatory requests are overdue, which documents remain unproduced, and whether the response quality has deteriorated over the last 3 months. Quantify the risk by regulatory body (Bursa Malaysia, Securities Commission, BNM) and build a waterfall chart for each overdue inquiry showing Received → Acknowledged → Documents Produced → Response Submitted → Closed. Present a structured RAG table with columns for Inquiry, Regulatory Body, Days Overdue, Document Gap, Risk Rating, and Recommended Action, and embed the waterfall charts beneath.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Upload /LEG_01_Legal_Matter_Register.xlsx to Analyst. Cross-tab analysis across the Matter Register, Risk Classification AND Statutory Deadlines tabs: assess whether the 7 slipping board resolutions create governance exposure at group level, and identify the 3 resolutions with the highest statutory penalty risk. Build a sparkline-style trend dashboard for resolution completion rate, average days-to-filing, and overdue percentage across the last 6 quarters. Flag resolutions with immediate statutory breach risk as Red, approaching deadline as Amber, and on-track as Green. Present as a RAG dashboard with the 3 sparkline charts and a short note on the likely implications for directors\' personal liability.'}
