        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open /LEG_04_Contract_Backlog_Tracker.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, pull data from THREE tabs simultaneously — Contract Backlog, Approval Pipeline AND Ageing Analysis — and build a new sheet called "Legal Matter RAG Dashboard". On that sheet, calculate for each of the 11 divisions: number of contracts pending, total unsigned value in MYR M, average days in queue, and percentage exceeding 60-day SLA. Add a group-level summary row at the top with KPI tiles for Total Backlog Count, Total Unsigned Value, Average Queue Days, and SLA Breach Rate. Insert a horizontal bar chart of unsigned value ranked worst to best, a clustered column chart of backlog count by division and age band (0-30, 31-60, 61-90, 90+ days), and a sparkline column for each division showing weekly backlog trend. Apply conditional formatting so divisions with more than 50 pending contracts are red, 25-50 amber, and below 25 green. The General Counsel presents this to the Board Governance Committee tomorrow.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open /LEG_05_Regulatory_Inquiry_Log.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, combine data from THREE tabs — Inquiry Tracking, Document Production AND Response Timeline — and create a new sheet called "Regulatory Response Dashboard". Build a waterfall chart for each of the 3 overdue regulatory inquiries showing the movement from Request Received to Documents Produced to Response Filed with days elapsed at each stage. Beside each waterfall, add a document-gap tile pulling from the Document Production tab (number of documents still outstanding) and a deadline-risk indicator pulling from the Response Timeline tab. Sort the inquiries from most overdue to least, highlight overdue inquiries in red banding, and embed a one-sentence status note beside each Red inquiry. Output a Board-pack-ready compliance dashboard sheet.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Open /LEG_01_Legal_Matter_Register.xlsx in Excel for Web. Using Copilot in Excel, cross-reference the Matter Register, Statutory Deadlines AND Risk Classification tabs to create a governance early-warning tracker on a new sheet called "Board Resolution Watchlist". Show resolution completion rate, average days-to-filing, overdue count, statutory penalty exposure, and compliance score for the group as 5 KPI tiles at the top. Below the tiles, build a line chart with secondary axis combining resolution completion rate (left axis, %) and overdue count (right axis, number) across the last 6 quarters. Add sparklines to each metric column so directors can scan governance trend at a glance. Calculate whether each trend is improving, flat, or deteriorating. Flag metrics deteriorating for 2 or more consecutive periods as Red, 1 period as Amber, and stable or improving as Green. Present as a compact RAG dashboard the General Counsel can review weekly.'}
