        {'instr':'Open a blank PowerPoint for Web file. Open the **Copilot pane** on the right. Paste the prompt below.', 'prompt':'Create a 5-slide Board Risk Committee deck on the audit findings and incident status using /RSK_04_Audit_Findings_Tracker.xlsx and /RSK_02_ERM_Framework.docx as source context. Cover: (1) risk posture overview and finding summary, (2) the 12 High-rated findings by division, (3) the 3 unnotified Q3 incidents, (4) immediate remediation actions, (5) decisions required from the Committee. Use a serious executive design with the Group navy theme. Then use Edit with Copilot to add concise speaker notes for each slide, drop in a chart on slide 1 showing findings by risk rating, and tighten any slide with more than 30 words.'},
        {'instr':'Open a blank PowerPoint for Web file. Open the **Copilot pane** on the right. Paste the prompt below.', 'prompt':'Create a 5-slide briefing deck for the CRO to use in discussions with divisional risk leads about the 14-day remediation sprint. Show the finding distribution, the resource bottlenecks, the sprint plan, expected closure targets, and escalation consequences for non-compliance. Use Edit with Copilot to flag the most material risk on each slide as Red, Amber, or Green, and to add detailed speaker notes. End with a slide titled "Division Risk Lead Commitments" with 3 short action bullets each.'},
        {'instr':'Open a blank PowerPoint for Web file. Open the **Copilot pane** on the right. Paste the prompt below.', 'prompt':'Build a 5-slide risk-appetite narrative deck that explains where the Group sits relative to stated appetite without understating the exposure, the 3 breached thresholds, what management is doing to restore compliance, and what the Board should monitor. Include one slide separating systemic control gaps from one-off process failures and one slide summarising the risk appetite recalibration proposal. Use Edit with Copilot to apply minimal text per slide, polished risk-governance design, and a closing slide titled "Risk Appetite Commitments for the Next Quarter".'}
