        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Help me prepare in parallel for the Board Risk Committee session in 14 days. Please do all 5 of the following at once and report back when each is ready: (1) draft a 2-page Word document titled \'Board Risk Committee Brief — Findings & Incidents\' using /RSK_04_Audit_Findings_Tracker.xlsx and /RSK_02_ERM_Framework.docx for context; (2) draft a second 1-page Word document titled \'CRO Opening Statement\' covering the 47 open findings, the 12 High-rated items, and the 3 unnotified Q3 incidents; (3) draft a confidential email to the Board Risk Committee members with the session purpose, agenda and pre-read instructions; (4) schedule a 30-minute Teams prep meeting with the CRO, Head of Internal Audit and Head of Enterprise Risk tomorrow at 8am to walk through the pack before the Committee convenes; (5) post a discreet message in the Risk Leadership Teams channel reminding the team that all incident communications are on hold until the Committee has met. Please confirm each task before sending external content. Use these named recipients consistently across the email task and the Teams meeting task — Hadar (Group CFO), Sasha (Group Chief of Staff), Daichi (Head of Investor Relations), Sonia (Head of Strategy), Will (Head of Risk) and Omar (Head of Procurement) — and adapt the precise distribution per sub-task to keep each communication focused on the right audience.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'After the Board Risk Committee has approved the remediation sprint, please complete in parallel: (1) draft the divisional risk lead notification email to all 11 divisions with the approved sprint rules and closure targets; (2) draft the incident notification memo for the Board covering the 3 Q3 events with approved language; (3) create a 14-day remediation sprint task list covering finding prioritisation, resource allocation, control testing, and progress reporting, then send it to the relevant divisional risk and audit leads; (4) schedule a 20-minute checkpoint Teams meeting for this afternoon with the risk leadership team; (5) update the audit findings tracker workbook with today\'s sprint status. Wait for my confirmation before sending Board-level communications. Use these named recipients consistently across the email task and the Teams meeting task — Hadar (Group CFO), Sasha (Group Chief of Staff), Daichi (Head of Investor Relations), Sonia (Head of Strategy), Will (Head of Risk) and Omar (Head of Procurement) — and adapt the precise distribution per sub-task to keep each communication focused on the right audience.'}
