        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'Help me prepare in parallel for next week\'s CEO strategy review on initiative acceleration and capex reallocation. Please do all 5 of the following at once and report back when each is ready: (1) draft a 2-page Word document titled \'CEO Strategy Review Brief — Initiative Acceleration & Capex\' using /STR_01_Strategy_Tracker.xlsx and /STR_02_Corporate_Plan.docx for context; (2) draft a second 1-page Word document titled \'Strategy Director Opening Statement\' covering the 3 delayed initiatives, the capex tension, and the FY2026 thesis refresh timeline; (3) draft an email to the Investment Committee members with the review purpose, agenda and pre-read instructions; (4) schedule a 30-minute Teams prep meeting with the Strategy Director, Head of Corporate Development and Head of Business Planning tomorrow at 8am to walk through the pack before the CEO session; (5) post a message in the Strategy Team Teams channel reminding the team of the 4-week thesis refresh deadline and requesting all divisional inputs by end of this week. Please confirm each task before sending external content. Use these named recipients consistently across the email task and the Teams meeting task — Hadar (Group CFO), Sasha (Group Chief of Staff), Daichi (Head of Investor Relations), Sonia (Head of Strategy), Will (Head of Risk) and Omar (Head of Procurement) — and adapt the precise distribution per sub-task to keep each communication focused on the right audience.'},
        {'instr':'', 'prompt':'After the CEO has approved the acceleration framework, please complete in parallel: (1) draft the divisional CEO notification email to all 11 divisions with the approved sequencing changes and new capex allocation parameters; (2) draft the Investment Committee resolution memo documenting the approved reallocation decisions; (3) create a 4-week strategy execution sprint task list covering initiative acceleration milestones, capex deployment checkpoints, FY2026 thesis sections, and stakeholder engagement, then send it to the relevant strategy team leads; (4) schedule a 20-minute checkpoint Teams meeting for this afternoon with the strategy leadership team; (5) update the strategy tracker workbook with today\'s acceleration decisions and revised milestones. Wait for my confirmation before sending to Investment Committee members. Use these named recipients consistently across the email task and the Teams meeting task — Hadar (Group CFO), Sasha (Group Chief of Staff), Daichi (Head of Investor Relations), Sonia (Head of Strategy), Will (Head of Risk) and Omar (Head of Procurement) — and adapt the precise distribution per sub-task to keep each communication focused on the right audience.'}
